╦[Left]
With fond memories of
MARTIN COOK
His guitar is silent 
His fingers no longer work
Those days have slipped away
All the hours that he played
Just a man who played his guitar.

[Center]
WITH HAPPY MEMORIES
JOYCE AND GERALD (GUS) STEELS
OF LOUGHTON, ESSEX
WHO LOVED PADSTOW AND
REGARDED IT AS THEIR SECOND HOME

[RIGHT]
In loving memory of
JOHN and EILEEN PEARCE
from Epsom, Surrey
who spent so many happy times
in and around Padstow"„
¶For fifty years I've loved this bay, and still I do I'm glad to say
So this isn't yet a memorial chair,  but one that I am pleased to share
But I suppose one day my sun will set
I only hope it won't be yet

Malcolm Wilkins
